(21, 21, '<p>Intraject is a syringue-like device that combines the action of:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-&nbsp;<strong>Radioporation</strong>&nbsp;(radiofrequency)&nbsp;<br />\r\n-&nbsp;<strong>Electroporation</strong>&nbsp;(moduladed electric pulses)<br />\r\n-&nbsp;<strong>Soft Surgery</strong>&nbsp;(plasma energy)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>for active ingredients transdermal delivery and skin rejuvenation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The main function of &quot;barrier&quot; of the skin resides almost entirely in the epidermis. Substances can cross the epidermis in intercellular and intracellular way, through the pilosebaceous apparatus and the eccrine glands . IntraJect is able to modify the permeability of the skin&rsquo;s barrier and allows to increase the therapeutic efficacy of skin formulations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Intraject : The advantages of transdermal delivery</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Clinically proven to work transdermal delivery and tissue activation for the vehiculation, the absorption of active elements through the skin</li>\r\n	<li>Increases efficiency in the delivery of active ingredients</li>\r\n	<li>Synergic action of electroporation, low-frequency ultrasound and radiofrequency to expand the transdermal spectrum to include the delivery of water-soluble molecules, peptides, proteins, and other macromolecules</li>\r\n	<li>Non invasive skin rejuvenation with transdermal delivery of PRP and fractional radiofrequency</li>\r\n	<li>Treats large areas in the same session, while maintaining the quality of the transfer during the duration of therapy</li>\r\n	<li>Minor amounts of active ingredient required</li>\r\n	<li>Increases local concentration of active ingredients</li>\r\n	<li>Increases speed of action and result</li>\r\n	<li>Prolongs the efficacy of the active ingredients</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>Intraject is a syringue-like device that combines the action of:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-&nbsp;<strong>Radioporation</strong>&nbsp;(radiofrequency)&nbsp;<br />\r\n-&nbsp;<strong>Electroporation</strong>&nbsp;(moduladed electric pulses)<br />\r\n-&nbsp;<strong>Soft Surgery</strong>&nbsp;(plasma energy)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>for active ingredients transdermal delivery and skin rejuvenation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The main function of &quot;barrier&quot; of the skin resides almost entirely in the epidermis. Substances can cross the epidermis in intercellular and intracellular way, through the pilosebaceous apparatus and the eccrine glands . IntraJect is able to modify the permeability of the skin&rsquo;s barrier and allows to increase the therapeutic efficacy of skin formulations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Intraject : The advantages of transdermal delivery</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Clinically proven to work transdermal delivery and tissue activation for the vehiculation, the absorption of active elements through the skin</li>\r\n	<li>Increases efficiency in the delivery of active ingredients</li>\r\n	<li>Synergic action of electroporation, low-frequency ultrasound and radiofrequency to expand the transdermal spectrum to include the delivery of water-soluble molecules, peptides, proteins, and other macromolecules</li>\r\n	<li>Non invasive skin rejuvenation with transdermal delivery of PRP and fractional radiofrequency</li>\r\n	<li>Treats large areas in the same session, while maintaining the quality of the transfer during the duration of therapy</li>\r\n	<li>Minor amounts of active ingredient required</li>\r\n	<li>Increases local concentration of active ingredients</li>\r\n	<li>Increases speed of action and result</li>\r\n	<li>Prolongs the efficacy of the active ingredients</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>Radioporation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Radioporation is able to transport metabolically active substances deep in the skin, due to the greater ability of transdermal absorption derived from high frequency electrical pulses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Electroporation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It uses modulated currents at low intensity that creates new extracellular pathways. Electroporation acts directly on the skin, temporarily increasing the permeability of the tissue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Soft surgery (plasma energy)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Uses plasma skin regeneration technology energy delivered from plasma rather than light or radiofrequency. The energy is uniformly absorbed by the skin, creating the right conditions and natural growth factors for new collagen and continuing skin regeneration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Applications:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Hair loss treatment<br />\r\n- Superficial and deep wrinkles<br />\r\n- Eye lid lifting<br />\r\n- Enlarged pores and acne scarring<br />\r\n- Hyperpigmentation<br />\r\n- Facial contouring<br />\r\n- Neck lifting<br />\r\n- Stretch marks</p>\r\n', '<p>Radioporation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Radioporation is able to transport metabolically active substances deep in the skin, due to the greater ability of transdermal absorption derived from high frequency electrical pulses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Electroporation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It uses modulated currents at low intensity that creates new extracellular pathways. Electroporation acts directly on the skin, temporarily increasing the permeability of the tissue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Soft surgery (plasma energy)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Uses plasma skin regeneration technology energy delivered from plasma rather than light or radiofrequency. The energy is uniformly absorbed by the skin, creating the right conditions and natural growth factors for new collagen and continuing skin regeneration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Applications:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Hair loss treatment<br />\r\n- Superficial and deep wrinkles<br />\r\n- Eye lid lifting<br />\r\n- Enlarged pores and acne scarring<br />\r\n- Hyperpigmentation<br />\r\n- Facial contouring<br />\r\n- Neck lifting<br />\r\n- Stretch marks</p>\r\n', '<p>General features</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Voltage supply:</strong>&nbsp;100 &divide; 230 Vac - 50/60Hz<br />\r\n<strong>Power consumption:</strong>&nbsp;160 W (operative)<br />\r\n<strong>Class and type:</strong>&nbsp;I BF<br />\r\n<strong>Dimensions:</strong>&nbsp;400(W) x 400(D) x 220(H) mm<br />\r\n<strong>Fuses:</strong>&nbsp;2x 2AF&nbsp; 250V</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mesowave PW e RW</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Frequency RW:</strong>&nbsp;500 kHz (amplitude modulated waveform)<br />\r\n<strong>Power energy RW (maximum):</strong>&nbsp;50W<br />\r\n<strong>Operation RW:</strong>&nbsp;continuous&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Frequency PW:</strong>&nbsp;1 kHz (amplitude modulated waveform with continuous component)<br />\r\n<strong>Power PW (maximum):</strong>&nbsp;10W<br />\r\n<strong>Operating mode PW:</strong>&nbsp;impulsato (3 sec on; 0,3 sec pause)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Detox</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Frequency:</strong>&nbsp;25 kHz<br />\r\n<strong>Maximum power emission:</strong>&nbsp;&lt;10 W<br />\r\n<strong>Emission dimension (spatula applicator):</strong>&nbsp;35x30 mm circa<br />\r\n<strong>Operating mode:</strong>&nbsp;continuous</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Plasmawave</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Working frequency of generator:</strong>&nbsp;87.8&nbsp; kHz<br />\r\n<strong>Maximum power of generator:</strong>&nbsp;60W circa<br />\r\n<strong>Operating mode:</strong>&nbsp;continuous</p>\r\n', '<p>General features</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Voltage supply:</strong>&nbsp;100 &divide; 230 Vac - 50/60Hz<br />\r\n<strong>Power consumption:</strong>&nbsp;160 W (operative)<br />\r\n<strong>Class and type:</strong>&nbsp;I BF<br />\r\n<strong>Dimensions:</strong>&nbsp;400(W) x 400(D) x 220(H) mm<br />\r\n<strong>Fuses:</strong>&nbsp;2x 2AF&nbsp; 250V</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mesowave PW e RW</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Frequency RW:</strong>&nbsp;500 kHz (amplitude modulated waveform)<br />\r\n<strong>Power energy RW (maximum):</strong>&nbsp;50W<br />\r\n<strong>Operation RW:</strong>&nbsp;continuous&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Frequency PW:</strong>&nbsp;1 kHz (amplitude modulated waveform with continuous component)<br />\r\n<strong>Power PW (maximum):</strong>&nbsp;10W<br />\r\n<strong>Operating mode PW:</strong>&nbsp;impulsato (3 sec on; 0,3 sec pause)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Detox</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Frequency:</strong>&nbsp;25 kHz<br />\r\n<strong>Maximum power emission:</strong>&nbsp;&lt;10 W<br />\r\n<strong>Emission dimension (spatula applicator):</strong>&nbsp;35x30 mm circa<br />\r\n<strong>Operating mode:</strong>&nbsp;continuous</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Plasmawave</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Working frequency of generator:</strong>&nbsp;87.8&nbsp; kHz<br />\r\n<strong>Maximum power of generator:</strong>&nbsp;60W circa<br />\r\n<strong>Operating mode:</strong>&nbsp;continuous</p>\r\n', '', ''),
(22, 22, '<p><strong>Mesotherm uses 6 different technologies for a 3D tissue rejuvenation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Microdermabrasion<br />\r\n- Vacuum<br />\r\n- Monopolar Radiofrequency<br />\r\n- Needling<br />\r\n- Electroporation<br />\r\n- LLLT (Low Level Laser Therapy)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nMicrodermabrasion</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It involves a flow of chemically inert corindone crystals (aluminium oxide) which are projected onto the skin by a compressed air system. The crystals transfer their kinetic energy to the cells in the first dermal layers, removing sebum and corneocytes. Microdermabrasion is suitable for all phototypes, including IV, V and VI, that should not undergo chemical peeling and laser resurfacing treatments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Monopolar Radiofrequency</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It acts by increasing the temperature in the dermis thanks to the so called Joule effect. When the tissue is heated above 60-65&deg;C, the collagen fibre is thermally denaturised and contracts, smoothing out the superficial wrinkles and immediately tightening the tissues. The long term effect of this induced heating process is the production of new collagen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Electroporation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It involves the local application of short, intense electrical impulses, which makes cells more permeable to the active ingredients, thanks to the temporary formation of pores on the plasmatic membranes. A true needleless injection which, depending on which product is used, has a biostimulating (e.g. vitamin and amino acid), draining, liporeduction action, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Needling</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is a dermatological regenerating technique. The microscopic punctures caused by the needles free growth factors (cytokines) and inflammatory induction factors (limphokines) into the epidermis, and in the dermis they free oxygen from the red globules and cell stimulating factors for platelets. The needling technique strongly tightens the skin, smoothing out wrinkles and improving scars, stretch marks and laxity in general.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Mesotherm uses 6 different technologies for a 3D tissue rejuvenation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Microdermabrasion<br />\r\n- Vacuum<br />\r\n- Monopolar Radiofrequency<br />\r\n- Needling<br />\r\n- Electroporation<br />\r\n- LLLT (Low Level Laser Therapy)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nMicrodermabrasion</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It involves a flow of chemically inert corindone crystals (aluminium oxide) which are projected onto the skin by a compressed air system. The crystals transfer their kinetic energy to the cells in the first dermal layers, removing sebum and corneocytes. Microdermabrasion is suitable for all phototypes, including IV, V and VI, that should not undergo chemical peeling and laser resurfacing treatments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Monopolar Radiofrequency</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It acts by increasing the temperature in the dermis thanks to the so called Joule effect. When the tissue is heated above 60-65&deg;C, the collagen fibre is thermally denaturised and contracts, smoothing out the superficial wrinkles and immediately tightening the tissues. The long term effect of this induced heating process is the production of new collagen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Electroporation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It involves the local application of short, intense electrical impulses, which makes cells more permeable to the active ingredients, thanks to the temporary formation of pores on the plasmatic membranes. A true needleless injection which, depending on which product is used, has a biostimulating (e.g. vitamin and amino acid), draining, liporeduction action, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Needling</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is a dermatological regenerating technique. The microscopic punctures caused by the needles free growth factors (cytokines) and inflammatory induction factors (limphokines) into the epidermis, and in the dermis they free oxygen from the red globules and cell stimulating factors for platelets. The needling technique strongly tightens the skin, smoothing out wrinkles and improving scars, stretch marks and laxity in general.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Mesotherm uses three different procedures for 3D skin rejuvenation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- mechanical thinning (<strong>microdermabrasion</strong>) of the stratum corneum to stimulate cell renewal;&nbsp;<br />\r\n- regeneration of the dermis by combining&nbsp;<strong>radiofrequency, needling and vacuum</strong>&nbsp;to stimulate a potent increase in tissue elasticity;&nbsp;<br />\r\n- biostimulation of the tissues by channelling mesotherapic cocktails using&nbsp;<strong>electroporation.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Clinical studies have demonstrated the effectiveness of these single technologies, and above all the effectiveness of a multifunctional synergic approach to treat skin imperfections.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mesotherm is perfectly safe and painless and no recovery time is needed. Occasionally the skin could show signs of reddening, which might last for a few hours. The skin is slightly more sensitive after the treatment, therefore a proper home cosmetic protocol (moisturising and protective products) is necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The number of treatments is determined according to the patient&rsquo;s age and skin condition, but normally the average number is at least 6 sessions. The results can be seen immediately after the first session, and moreover Mesotherm treatments can be combined with other aesthetic treatments, such as filler, Botox, etc.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Mesotherm uses three different procedures for 3D skin rejuvenation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- mechanical thinning (<strong>microdermabrasion</strong>) of the stratum corneum to stimulate cell renewal;&nbsp;<br />\r\n- regeneration of the dermis by combining&nbsp;<strong>radiofrequency, needling and vacuum</strong>&nbsp;to stimulate a potent increase in tissue elasticity;&nbsp;<br />\r\n- biostimulation of the tissues by channelling mesotherapic cocktails using&nbsp;<strong>electroporation.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Clinical studies have demonstrated the effectiveness of these single technologies, and above all the effectiveness of a multifunctional synergic approach to treat skin imperfections.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mesotherm is perfectly safe and painless and no recovery time is needed. Occasionally the skin could show signs of reddening, which might last for a few hours. The skin is slightly more sensitive after the treatment, therefore a proper home cosmetic protocol (moisturising and protective products) is necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The number of treatments is determined according to the patient&rsquo;s age and skin condition, but normally the average number is at least 6 sessions. The results can be seen immediately after the first session, and moreover Mesotherm treatments can be combined with other aesthetic treatments, such as filler, Botox, etc.</p>\r\n', '<p>General specifications</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Treatment activation:&nbsp;</strong>button touch-screen<br />\r\n<strong>Power supply:&nbsp;</strong>230 Vac 50/60 Hz<br />\r\n<strong>Output:&nbsp;</strong>150 W (max)<br />\r\n<strong>Dimensions:&nbsp;</strong>320x650x580xmm (HxLxD)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dermoabrasion</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Abrasion material:&nbsp;</strong>aluminium oxide<br />\r\n<strong>Suction:&nbsp;</strong>50 kPa (max)<br />\r\n<strong>Laser wavelenght:&nbsp;</strong>635 nm<br />\r\n<strong>Laser power:&nbsp;</strong>1 mW<br />\r\n<strong>Laser class:&nbsp;</strong>2</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Radiofrequency</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>RF handpiece functions:</strong>&nbsp;unipolar<br />\r\n<strong>Unipolar function frequency:&nbsp;</strong>from 350 Hz ut to 1 MHz<br />\r\n<strong>Power:&nbsp;</strong>50 W (max)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Electroporation</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Frequency:&nbsp;</strong>1.1 KHz modulated signal in amplitude with modulating sinusoidal frequency 0.5 Hz<br />\r\n<strong>Maximun intensity on the plate:&nbsp;</strong>0.8 mA for 10 cm2</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Body/face suction</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Suction:&nbsp;</strong>50 kPa (max)<br />\r\n<strong>Mode:&nbsp;</strong>continued/pulsed</p>\r\n', '<p>General specifications</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Treatment activation:&nbsp;</strong>button touch-screen<br />\r\n<strong>Power supply:&nbsp;</strong>230 Vac 50/60 Hz<br />\r\n<strong>Output:&nbsp;</strong>150 W (max)<br />\r\n<strong>Dimensions:&nbsp;</strong>320x650x580xmm (HxLxD)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dermoabrasion</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Abrasion material:&nbsp;</strong>aluminium oxide<br />\r\n<strong>Suction:&nbsp;</strong>50 kPa (max)<br />\r\n<strong>Laser wavelenght:&nbsp;</strong>635 nm<br />\r\n<strong>Laser power:&nbsp;</strong>1 mW<br />\r\n<strong>Laser class:&nbsp;</strong>2</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Radiofrequency</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>RF handpiece functions:</strong>&nbsp;unipolar<br />\r\n<strong>Unipolar function frequency:&nbsp;</strong>from 350 Hz ut to 1 MHz<br />\r\n<strong>Power:&nbsp;</strong>50 W (max)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Electroporation</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Frequency:&nbsp;</strong>1.1 KHz modulated signal in amplitude with modulating sinusoidal frequency 0.5 Hz<br />\r\n<strong>Maximun intensity on the plate:&nbsp;</strong>0.8 mA for 10 cm2</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Body/face suction</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Suction:&nbsp;</strong>50 kPa (max)<br />\r\n<strong>Mode:&nbsp;</strong>continued/pulsed</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>David Kist et al.&nbsp;<em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;38:150&ndash;154 (2006)</li>\r\n	<li>Uwe Paasch,&nbsp;<em>Journal of the german society of dermatology</em>&nbsp;2009, 7, 196-203</li>\r\n	<li>Pavan K. Nootheti et al.&nbsp;<em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;38:908&ndash;912 (2006)</li>\r\n	<li>Lori Brightman,&nbsp;<em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;41:791&ndash;798 (2009)</li>\r\n	<li>Rinaldi et al.&nbsp;<em>Journal of plastic dermatology</em>&nbsp;2006, p. 17-22</li>\r\n	<li>Basil M. Hantash et al.<em>&nbsp;Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;41:1&ndash;9 (2009)</li>\r\n	<li>Mohamed L. Elsaie et al.&nbsp;<em>Dermatologic Surgery</em>&nbsp;2010;36:577&ndash;589</li>\r\n	<li>Josep