(26, 26, '<p><strong>Thermopeel MRF uses 5 different technologies for a 3D tissue rejuvenation:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Microdermabrasion<br />\r\n- Low Energy Infrared Laser<br />\r\n- Vacuum Aspiration<br />\r\n- Bipolar Radiofrequency&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Electroporation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Microdermabrasion</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It exploits the physical action of inert corindone crystals (aluminium oxide) to exfoliate the skin. Contemporary a low energy Infrared laser beam penetrates into the tissue, stimulating cellular metabolism and speeding up tissue renewal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bipolar Radiofrequency</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is associated with the vacuum system, increases the temperature deep into the dermis, causing the collagen fibre contraction, thus smoothing out wrinkles and immediately tightening tissues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Electroporation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It makes the cells more permeable to the active ingredients, thanks to the temporary formation of pores on the cell membranes. A true needleless injection which, depending on which product is used, has a biostimulating, draining, liporeduction action, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Diode laser</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Laser biostimulation is a method of cell stimulation as a result of tissue radiation with laser light. Laser energy in tissue is absorbed through cytochrome cells.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pulsed vacuum massage</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A suction and pressure pump allows for the performance of a pulsed vacuum massage on the skin&#39;s surface thereby sucking it between the two inner spatulas on the head.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Thermopeel MRF uses 5 different technologies for a 3D tissue rejuvenation:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Microdermabrasion<br />\r\n- Low Energy Infrared Laser<br />\r\n- Vacuum Aspiration<br />\r\n- Bipolar Radiofrequency&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Electroporation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Microdermabrasion</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It exploits the physical action of inert corindone crystals (aluminium oxide) to exfoliate the skin. Contemporary a low energy Infrared laser beam penetrates into the tissue, stimulating cellular metabolism and speeding up tissue renewal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bipolar Radiofrequency</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is associated with the vacuum system, increases the temperature deep into the dermis, causing the collagen fibre contraction, thus smoothing out wrinkles and immediately tightening tissues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Electroporation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It makes the cells more permeable to the active ingredients, thanks to the temporary formation of pores on the cell membranes. A true needleless injection which, depending on which product is used, has a biostimulating, draining, liporeduction action, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Diode laser</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Laser biostimulation is a method of cell stimulation as a result of tissue radiation with laser light. Laser energy in tissue is absorbed through cytochrome cells.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pulsed vacuum massage</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A suction and pressure pump allows for the performance of a pulsed vacuum massage on the skin&#39;s surface thereby sucking it between the two inner spatulas on the head.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>ThermoPeel is a non- invasive, simple to use device, able to treat the following imperfections:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Superficial and deep wrinkles&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Hyperkeratosis&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Sun-damaged skin&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Small wrinkles&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Acne and skin impurities&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Enlarged pores&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Rough and thickened skin&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Hyperpigmentation marks<br />\r\n- Stretch marks&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Acne scars<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThermopeel MRF uses three different procedures for a 3D skin rejuvenation:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>the&nbsp;<strong>Abralase</strong>&nbsp;<strong>technique</strong>&nbsp;combines microdermabrasion and soft laser for a fast skin regeneration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<strong>Tightening</strong>&nbsp;option combines bipolar radiofrequency and pulsated vacuum massage, to increase skin elasticity and reduce wrinkles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<strong>Mesoskin technique</strong>&nbsp;provides a deep biostimulation of the tissues by channelling mesotherapic cocktails using electroporation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thermopeel MRF provides very fast and effective treatment. A complete facial peeling requires approximately 10/15 minutes. A full treatment combining different technologies requires from 30 to 45 minutes, depending on the extent of the area being treated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The number of treatments is determined according to the patient&rsquo;s age and skin condition, but normally the average number is at least 6 sessions. The results can be seen immediately after the first session.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>ThermoPeel is a non- invasive, simple to use device, able to treat the following imperfections:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Superficial and deep wrinkles&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Hyperkeratosis&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Sun-damaged skin&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Small wrinkles&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Acne and skin impurities&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Enlarged pores&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Rough and thickened skin&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Hyperpigmentation marks<br />\r\n- Stretch marks&nbsp;<br />\r\n- Acne scars<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThermopeel MRF uses three different procedures for a 3D skin rejuvenation:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>the&nbsp;<strong>Abralase</strong>&nbsp;<strong>technique</strong>&nbsp;combines microdermabrasion and soft laser for a fast skin regeneration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<strong>Tightening</strong>&nbsp;option combines bipolar radiofrequency and pulsated vacuum massage, to increase skin elasticity and reduce wrinkles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<strong>Mesoskin technique</strong>&nbsp;provides a deep biostimulation of the tissues by channelling mesotherapic cocktails using electroporation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thermopeel MRF provides very fast and effective treatment. A complete facial peeling requires approximately 10/15 minutes. A full treatment combining different technologies requires from 30 to 45 minutes, depending on the extent of the area being treated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The number of treatments is determined according to the patient&rsquo;s age and skin condition, but normally the average number is at least 6 sessions. The results can be seen immediately after the first session.</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>DERMOABRASION</strong><br />\r\n	Material: Ossido di Alluminio<br />\r\n	Suction: 50kPa (Max)<br />\r\n	Lenght of the laser wave: 635nm<br />\r\n	Laser power: 1mW<br />\r\n	Laser Class: 2<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>RADIOFREQUENCY</strong><br />\r\n	RF: Bipolar<br />\r\n	Frequency: Up to 1 MHz<br />\r\n	Power: 50W (max)<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>ELECTROPORATION</strong><br />\r\n	Frequency: 1,1 KHz<br />\r\n	Max Intensity: 0.8 mA per 10 cm&sup2;<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>VACUUM FACE/BODY</strong><br />\r\n	Suction: 50 kPa (max)<br />\r\n	Mode: pulsed/continous<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Energy: D230 Vac 50/60Hz<br />\r\n	Power: 150W<br />\r\n	Dimensions: 320x650x580 mm<br />\r\n	Weight: 20 kg</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>DERMOABRASION</strong><br />\r\n	Material: Ossido di Alluminio<br />\r\n	Suction: 50kPa (Max)<br />\r\n	Lenght of the laser wave: 635nm<br />\r\n	Laser power: 1mW<br />\r\n	Laser Class: 2<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>RADIOFREQUENCY</strong><br />\r\n	RF: Bipolar<br />\r\n	Frequency: Up to 1 MHz<br />\r\n	Power: 50W (max)<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>ELECTROPORATION</strong><br />\r\n	Frequency: 1,1 KHz<br />\r\n	Max Intensity: 0.8 mA per 10 cm&sup2;<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>VACUUM FACE/BODY</strong><br />\r\n	Suction: 50 kPa (max)<br />\r\n	Mode: pulsed/continous<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	Energy: D230 Vac 50/60Hz<br />\r\n	Power: 150W<br />\r\n	Dimensions: 320x650x580 mm<br />\r\n	Weight: 20 kg</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', ''),
(27, 27, '<p><strong>Supreme includes the CPL (Calibrated Pulsed Light) hair removal system and diode laser handpiece.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>CPL pulsed light</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Calibrated Pulsed Light applicator is simple and efficient to operate; controls are within easy reach and important user information is clearly displayed on the color monitor, including energy delivered and treatment setting with true energy fluence up to 30 J/cm2. Most importantly, is able to function at a very high speed, giving 2 shots per second.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Diode Laser</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supreme Diode handpiece provides permanent hair reduction using cutting-edge high-power diode technology. It guarantees a rapid, non-invasive procedure, with no downtime, able to treat all skin types (I-VI), as well as tanned skin and pseudofolliculitis barbae. It utilizes a 1cm square sapphire tip that actively cools before, during and after treatment.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Supreme includes the CPL (Calibrated Pulsed Light) hair removal system and diode laser handpiece.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>CPL pulsed light</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Calibrated Pulsed Light applicator is simple and efficient to operate; controls are within easy reach and important user information is clearly displayed on the color monitor, including energy delivered and treatment setting with true energy fluence up to 30 J/cm2. Most importantly, is able to function at a very high speed, giving 2 shots per second.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Diode Laser</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supreme Diode handpiece provides permanent hair reduction using cutting-edge high-power diode technology. It guarantees a rapid, non-invasive procedure, with no downtime, able to treat all skin types (I-VI), as well as tanned skin and pseudofolliculitis barbae. It utilizes a 1cm square sapphire tip that actively cools before, during and after treatment.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Laser technology has been used for an increasing number of cosmetic treatments.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Examples include hair reduction, skin rejuvenation wrinkle reduction, treatment of acne, removal of pigmented blemishes, treatment of vascular lesions and treatment of nail fungus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supreme grants ultimate flexibility to treat a wide variety of patient-requested procedures. The system&rsquo;s modular applicators are designed to offer effective and reliable results with minimal to no patient discomfort and downtime. No single device will do more than Supreme.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Laser technology has been used for an increasing number of cosmetic treatments.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Examples include hair reduction, skin rejuvenation wrinkle reduction, treatment of acne, removal of pigmented blemishes, treatment of vascular lesions and treatment of nail fungus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supreme grants ultimate flexibility to treat a wide variety of patient-requested procedures. The system&rsquo;s modular applicators are designed to offer effective and reliable results with minimal to no patient discomfort and downtime. No single device will do more than Supreme.</p>\r\n', '<p>Dimensions: 600x560x360 mm<br />\r\nWeight: 35 kg<br />\r\nCooling system: water, air, thermoelectric integrated<br />\r\nInterface: touch-screen color LCD 7&rsquo;&rsquo;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Laser</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wavelenght: 808 nm<br />\r\nPulse duration: 60 ms maximum<br />\r\nRepetition rate: variable from 1 up to 10 Hz<br />\r\nEnergy density: variable up to 40 J/cm2<br />\r\nSpot size: 0.9 x 0.9 cm2&nbsp;standard<br />\r\nSkin cooling: water and ice type integrated<br />\r\nExpected lifetime: 20.000.000</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>CPL pulsed light</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Source: Xenon lamp<br />\r\nSpectrum of emission: 600 &ndash; 1100 nm; 600 &ndash; 950 nm; 650 &ndash; 950 nm; 695 &ndash; 1100 nm; 755 &ndash; 1100 nm<br />\r\nEnergy per pulse: 26 J/cm2<br />\r\nPulse duration: single from 10 to 50 ms<br />\r\nDelay between pulse: 40 ms<br />\r\nNumber of pulses: 1 to 5<br />\r\nRepetition rate: 3 Hz (max)<br />\r\nTreatment area: 50,1 x 10 mm (5,01 cm2)<br />\r\nEmission control: footswitch and handpiece switch<br />\r\nCooling system: thermoelectric integrated<br />\r\nFlash numbers: 50.000</p>\r\n', '<p>Dimensions: 600x560x360 mm<br />\r\nWeight: 35 kg<br />\r\nCooling system: water, air, thermoelectric integrated<br />\r\nInterface: touch-screen color LCD 7&rsquo;&rsquo;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Laser</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wavelenght: 808 nm<br />\r\nPulse duration: 60 ms maximum<br />\r\nRepetition rate: variable from 1 up to 10 Hz<br />\r\nEnergy density: variable up to 40 J/cm2<br />\r\nSpot size: 0.9 x 0.9 cm2&nbsp;standard<br />\r\nSkin cooling: water and ice type integrated<br />\r\nExpected lifetime: 20.000.000</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>CPL pulsed light</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Source: Xenon lamp<br />\r\nSpectrum of emission: 600 &ndash; 1100 nm; 600 &ndash; 950 nm; 650 &ndash; 950 nm; 695 &ndash; 1100 nm; 755 &ndash; 1100 nm<br />\r\nEnergy per pulse: 26 J/cm2<br />\r\nPulse duration: single from 10 to 50 ms<br />\r\nDelay between pulse: 40 ms<br />\r\nNumber of pulses: 1 to 5<br />\r\nRepetition rate: 3 Hz (max)<br />\r\nTreatment area: 50,1 x 10 mm (5,01 cm2)<br />\r\nEmission control: footswitch and handpiece switch<br />\r\nCooling system: thermoelectric integrated<br />\r\nFlash numbers: 50.000</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Journal of Cutaneous Laser Therapy</em>&nbsp;2000; 2: 63-71.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Dermatol. Surg.</em>&nbsp;2006; 32: 234-240.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Journal of Cosmetic and Laser Therapy</em>&nbsp;2005; 7: 33-38.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2003; 32: 405-412.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2002; 30: 82-85.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Dermatol Surg</em>&nbsp;2010; 36: 829-840.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2002; 30: 298-305.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2005; 37: 9-13.</li>\r\n	<li><em>The British Association of Plastic Surgeons</em>&nbsp;2004; 57: 453-455.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Dermatol Surg</em>&nbsp;2008; 34: 672-680.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2003; 32: 42-45.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2005; 37: 333-342.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Arch Dermatol</em>&nbsp;2001; vol 137.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Medical Laser Application</em>&nbsp;2005; 20: 255-266.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2004; 35: 68-76.</li>\r\n	<li><em>J. Plast. Reconstr. Surg.</em>&nbsp;2007; 31: 123-128.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;1998; 22: 223-227.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Dermatologic clinics</em>&nbsp;1997; 15: 397-407.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li><em>Journal of Cutaneous Laser Therapy</em>&nbsp;2000; 2: 63-71.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Dermatol. Surg.</em>&nbsp;2006; 32: 234-240.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Journal of Cosmetic and Laser Therapy</em>&nbsp;2005; 7: 33-38.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2003; 32: 405-412.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2002; 30: 82-85.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Dermatol Surg</em>&nbsp;2010; 36: 829-840.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2002; 30: 298-305.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2005; 37: 9-13.</li>\r\n	<li><em>The British Association of Plastic Surgeons</em>&nbsp;2004; 57: 453-455.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Dermatol Surg</em>&nbsp;2008; 34: 672-680.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2003; 32: 42-45.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2005; 37: 333-342.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Arch Dermatol</em>&nbsp;2001; vol 137.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Medical Laser Application</em>&nbsp;2005; 20: 255-266.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;2004; 35: 68-76.</li>\r\n	<li><em>J. Plast. Reconstr. Surg.</em>&nbsp;2007; 31: 123-128.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Lasers in Surgery and Medicine</em>&nbsp;1998; 22: 223-227.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Dermatologic clinics</em>&nbsp;1997; 15: 397-407.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
(28, 28, '<p><strong>Perfecy press is a modern pressotherapy.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Though the application of muscular pressure, it improves lymphatic circulation and at the same time performs as pleasant massage to the legs, improving also the overall blood circulation.&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis treatment is ideal for people suffering from any circulatory disorder, prone to water retention, with swollen ankles or heavy and painful legs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many more conditions benefit from the perfect press treatment, including: cellulite, fatigue, heavy legs, damages or lesions from sports activities, muscular sprains, leg ulcers, varicose veins, burns lymphatic edema and legs needing tone and shape up.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Perfecy press is a modern pressotherapy.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Though the application of muscular pressure, it improves lymphatic circulation and at the same time performs as pleasant massage to the legs, improving also the overall blood circulation.&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis treatment is ideal for people suffering from any circulatory disorder, prone to water retention, with swollen ankles or heavy and painful legs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many more conditions benefit from the perfect press treatment, including: cellulite, fatigue, heavy legs, damages or lesions from sports activities, muscular sprains, leg ulcers, varicose veins, burns lymphatic edema and legs needing tone and shape up.</p>\r\n', '<p>Perfect Press is recommended for:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>- Stress and chronic tension relief</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Need to relax</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Painful spasms relief</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Muscular sprains</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Athletic efforts lesions and distortions</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Bursitis and tendonitis</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Pregnancy and post-partum discomforts</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Lymphatic drainage and cellulite</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Need to improve blood circulation</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nDuring its usage, Perfect Press stimulates the lymphatic circulation, expands capillaries, improves the ability to inhale oxygen, for it to reach deeply in the tissues and in the interspaces, increases oxygenation in blood and activates cellular metabolism.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Perfect Press is used on lower limbs, including buttocks, on the hips, thighs, and on the lower<br />\r\nabdomen.<br />\r\nIt is also possible to treat arms, using specially designed armbands.</p>\r\n', '<p>Perfect Press is recommended for:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>- Stress and chronic tension relief</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Need to relax</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Painful spasms relief</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Muscular sprains</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Athletic efforts lesions and distortions</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Bursitis and tendonitis</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Pregnancy and post-partum discomforts</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Lymphatic drainage and cellulite</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- Need to improve blood circulation</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nDuring its usage, Perfect Press stimulates the lymphatic circulation, expands capillaries, improves the ability to inhale oxygen, for it to reach deeply in the tissues and in the interspaces, increases oxygenation in blood and activates cellular metabolism.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Perfect Press is used on lower limbs, including buttocks, on the hips, thighs, and on the lower<br />\r\nabdomen.<br />\r\nIt is also possible to treat arms, using specially designed armbands.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Mains Voltage</strong>: 220-2240v/50-60Hz<br />\r\n<strong>Power Max</strong>: 220 VA<br />\r\n<strong>Pressure Max</strong>: 200mmHg<br />\r\n<strong>Class</strong>: I B<br />\r\n<strong>Dimension</strong>: 48 x30 x15 cm (LxDxH)&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Weight</strong>: 15 kg</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Mains Voltage</strong>: 220-2240v/50-60Hz<br />\r\n<strong>Power Max</strong>: 220 VA<br />\r\n<strong>Pressure Max</strong>: 200mmHg<br />\r\n<strong>Class</strong>: I B<br />\r\n<strong>Dimension</strong>: 48 x30 x15 cm (LxDxH)&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Weight</strong>: 15 kg</p>\r\n', '', '');
